# ============================================================
# Observed marginal cooling capacity from fast matched benchmark
#
# Purpose:
#   Convert observed matched cooling benefit curves into
#   marginal cooling capacity curves.
#
# Definition:
#   Cooling benefit:
#       CB(EVI_k) = LST'_low-ref - LST'_target-bin
#
#   Marginal cooling capacity:
#       MCC(EVI_k) = [CB(EVI_k) - CB(EVI_{k-1})] / [EVI_k - EVI_{k-1}]
#
# Unit:
#   °C per unit EVI
#
# Interpretation:
#   Positive MCC means increasing EVI from the previous bin to the current bin
#   provides additional cooling.
#
#   Declining MCC means additional EVI still may cool, but the extra cooling
#   per unit EVI becomes weaker.
# ============================================================

