# ============================================================
# Observed trajectory matching analogue of ML timing-shift metrics
#
# Goal:
#   Find a representative city-year where early-EVI and late-EVI trajectories
#   have similar climate/static/EVI-amount/pre-LST backgrounds,
#   then compare the same metrics used in ML counterfactual simulation:
#
#   1) warm-season P95 LST anomaly
#   2) cumulative heat load
#   3) peak timing
#
# Sign convention, aligned with ML simulation:
#   observed_d_warm_p95  = early_P95 - late_P95
#   observed_d_heat_load = early_heat_load - late_heat_load
#   observed_d_peak_time = early_peak_time - late_peak_time
#
# Interpretation:
#   d_warm_p95 < 0   => early EVI is cooler for P95
#   d_heat_load < 0  => early EVI has lower heat load
#   d_peak_time > 0  => early EVI delays LST peak
#
# This is an observed matched analogue, not causal proof.
# ============================================================

